<UserControl x:Class="EO.Wpf.Demo.Demos.Buttons.CheckBox"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             xmlns:eo="http://schemas.essentialobjects.com/wpf/"
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             d:DesignHeight="300" d:DesignWidth="300">
    <StackPanel>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,0,0,10">
            EO.Wpf CheckBox is very similar to the built-in WPF CheckBox control.
            It offers the ability to switch themes dynamically, you can use the Theme menu 
            to switch themes and see it in action. It also offers a convenient
            CheckState property to access the state value as an enum.
        </TextBlock>
        <eo:CheckBox HorizontalAlignment="Left">This is a check box.</eo:CheckBox>
    </StackPanel>
</UserControl>
